import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.countplot(y='country', data=data, order=data['country'].value_counts().index, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.ylabel('Country')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", data=data, order=data['state'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set(xlabel='State/Province', ylabel='Number of Airports')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by state/province?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=800, background_color='white', min_font_size=10).generate(' '.join(data['name']))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.tight_layout(pad=0)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport codes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport Codes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
